President Trump and Secretary Mnuchin held a meeting to discuss the Foreign Investment Risk Review Modernization Act (FIRRMA) and its importance in protecting American technology and intellectual property. The legislation grants the Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States (CFIUS) greater authority to review foreign ownership of American firms with critical technology and intellectual property. The President emphasized the need to protect American intellectual property from theft and the negative impact it has on the economy and national security. Senators and Representatives in attendance expressed their support for the legislation and praised the administration's efforts in addressing the threat posed by China. Secretary Mnuchin highlighted the importance of the legislation and stated that the pilot program will be launched soon, with full implementation expected next year. Overall, the meeting celebrated the passage of FIRRMA and the collaboration between the Senate, the House, and the administration.